WE ACTUALLY WASTE
A LOT OF WATER -

00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:03.000
EVERYBODY WANTING TO HAVE
NICE, LUSH BLUEGRASS LAWNS,

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:05.000
WHICH ARE FINE IF YOU
ACTUALLY LIVE IN KENTUCKY

00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:06.000
AND IT RAINS ENOUGH.

00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:09.000
BUT WHEN YOU'RE IN A PLACE
LIKE DENVER OR SOME PLACE

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:12.000
THAT'S ACTUALLY A
DESERT, YOU JUST DON'T

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:15.000
HAVE ENOUGH WATER TO
SUPPORT THAT NATURALLY.

00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:17.000
SO WE'RE REPLACING THESE
LUSH LAWNS WITH EITHER

00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:19.000
NATIVE GRASSES THAT
ARE ACTUALLY BETTER AT

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:22.000
SURVIVING UNDER MORE
DROUGHT CONDITIONS

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:24.000
OR, EVEN BETTER,
DOING XERISCAPING

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:26.000
USING ALL NATIVE PLANTS
AS A WAY TO CONSERVE,

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:29.000
YOU KNOW, SPREADING
OUT WATER.

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:32.000
WATER POLLUTION IS
ALSO A MAJOR CONCERN.

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:35.000
THE WATER USED IN
FARMING AND AGRICULTURE

00:08:35.000 --> 00:08:38.000
CAN HAVE SERIOUS AND LONG
LASTING CONSEQUENCES.

00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:41.000
UNFORTUNATELY WHEN WATER
IS SUPPLIED TO FARM LAND

00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:43.000
IT'S ACTUALLY PICKING UP
THINGS LIKE FERTILIZER

00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:45.000
AND HERBICIDES AND THINGS
LIKE THAT WHICH ARE HARD TO

00:08:46.000 --> 00:08:48.000
GET BACK OUT OF THE WATER,
SO IT'S NOT LIKE YOU JUST

00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:51.000
LET IT EVAPORATE AND IT
RE-ENTERS THE WHOLE SYSTEM

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:53.000
AND IS CLEANED UP.

00:08:53.000 --> 00:08:56.000
CONTAMINATED WATER RE-ENTERS
THE SYSTEM IN OUR RIVERS

00:08:56.000 --> 00:08:59.000
AND STREAMS, AFFECTING
LIFE IN THE WATER,

00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:02.000
AND SOMETIMES
THE WATER WE DRINK.

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:11.000
CITY SEWAGE AND INDUSTRIAL
WASTE DISCHARGED INTO THE

00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:15.000
RIVERS ARE MAJOR CULPRITS
OF WATER POLLUTION.

00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:17.000
THE EFFECTS OF WATER
POLLUTION ARE NOT ONLY

00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:20.000
DEVASTATING TO PEOPLE, BUT
ALSO TO ANIMALS, FISH,

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:23.000
AND BIRDS.

00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:25.000
ANOTHER ENVIRONMENTAL
ISSUE THAT INVOLVES

00:09:25.000 --> 00:09:28.000
BALANCING THE GROWING NEED
FOR NATURAL RESOURCES WITH

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:31.000
DEPLETION AND POLLUTION
IS DEFORESTATION.

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:34.000
DEFORESTATION IS THE
PERMANENT DESTRUCTION OF

00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:37.000
OUR INDIGENOUS FORESTS AND
WOODLANDS, AND ONE OF THE

00:09:37.000 --> 00:09:40.000
MAJOR CONCERNS IS THE RATE
AT WHICH DEFORESTATION IS

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:43.000
OCCURRING THROUGHOUT THE
WORLD LARGELY DUE TO THE

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:48.000
GROWING NEEDS FOR FARMING,
RANCHING AND MINING.

00:09:48.000 --> 00:09:50.000
THERE ARE MANY
TYPES OF FORESTS:

00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:52.000
TEMPERATE FORESTS

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:54.000
RAINFORESTS

00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:55.000
MANGROVE SWAMPS

00:09:55.000 --> 00:09:57.000
AND THEY ALL HAVE MANY
IMPORTANT FUNCTIONS

00:09:57.000 --> 00:09:59.000
IN THE ENVIRONMENT.

00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:02.000
THEY PROVIDE HABITAT FOR
MANY IMPORTANT SPECIES,

00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:05.000
HELP REPLENISH
NUTRIENTS IN THE LAND,

00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:09.000
PROVIDE US IMPORTANT TIMBER
AND WOOD BASED PRODUCTS,

00:10:09.000 --> 00:10:11.000
HELP PREVENT EROSION
AND LANDSLIDES,

00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:14.000
AND THEY PRODUCE OXYGEN
WHILE TRAPPING CARBON

00:10:14.000 --> 00:10:17.000
AND OTHER POLLUTANTS
IN THE AIR.

00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:19.000
IT IS ESTIMATED THAT
80% OF THE WORLD'S

00:10:19.000 --> 00:10:23.000
ORIGINAL FOREST HAS BEEN
CLEARED OR DEGRADED.

00:10:23.000 --> 00:10:25.000
AND WHILE NEW AWARENESS
IS BEGINNING TO PROTECT

00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:28.000
MANY FORESTS, IRRESPONSIBLE
CLEAR CUTTING CONTINUES

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:32.000
AT AN ALARMING RATE.

