BY REMOVING THE FOREST
THROUGH CLEAR CUTTING

00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:38.000
YOU BEGIN TO DRAMATICALLY
CHANGE THOSE SLOPES.

00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:40.000
YOU DRAMATICALLY CHANGE
THE RESPONSE TO RAINFALL,

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:43.000
TO EROSION, YOU BEGIN TO
STRIP SOME OF THE SOILS.

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:47.000
SOILS TAKE THOUSANDS
TO TENS OF THOUSANDS OR

00:10:47.000 --> 00:10:49.000
HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS OF
YEARS TO FORM SO IF YOU

00:10:49.000 --> 00:10:52.000
REMOVE THEM BY STRIPPING
AN AREA OF ITS VEGETATION,

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:56.000
ENHANCING EROSION, THIS IS
NOT A SYSTEM - THAT IS,

00:10:56.000 --> 00:11:00.000
A SOIL - THAT'S GOING TO
COME BACK VERY QUICKLY

00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:04.000
EVEN IF YOU WERE TO ALLOW
THE FORESTS TO GROW AGAIN

00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:06.000
BECAUSE SOILS TAKE
THOUSANDS AND THOUSANDS

00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:08.000
OF YEARS TO FORM.

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:11.000
WITHOUT THE NUTRIENT-RICH
SOIL AND TREES,

00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:14.000
THE BALANCE OF THIS
ECOSYSTEM IS DISRUPTED.

00:11:14.000 --> 00:11:17.000
IF THE REGION CANNOT
HOLD AS MUCH WATER,

00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:18.000
MANY OF THE PLANTS
AND ANIMALS THAT

00:11:18.000 --> 00:11:21.000
DEPEND ON THE FOREST
CAN GO EXTINCT.

00:11:22.000 --> 00:11:24.000
SO WHAT HAPPENS IS THAT
YOU DON'T HAVE THOSE

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:26.000
NORMAL "GIVE AND TAKE"
CYCLES THAT YOU HAVE

00:11:26.000 --> 00:11:29.000
IN FORESTED AREAS
WHERE THERE'S PLANTS

00:11:29.000 --> 00:11:31.000
THAT ARE TAKING
NUTRIENTS BUT

00:11:31.000 --> 00:11:33.000
THEY'RE ALSO GIVING
NUTRIENTS BACK.

00:11:33.000 --> 00:11:36.000
IN THESE AREAS THERE'S
NO PLANTS AND THERE'S

00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:38.000
NO WATER SO THE CYCLE
CAN'T TAKE PLACE AND

00:11:38.000 --> 00:11:41.000
EVENTUALLY IT'S JUST
UNABLE TO SUPPORT LIFE

00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:45.000
AND IT BECOMES THIS
DRY AND BARREN PLACE.

